zt: Wie hat der (massen-)kulturelle Durchbruch digitaler Spiele andere Disziplinen beeinflusst, etwa Literatur-, Kunst-, Theater- und Filmwissenschaft?Mit Beiträgen von u.a. Ian Bogost, Thomas Hensel, Jesse Schell, Stephan Schwingeler und Eric Zimmerman.  aGame studies have been established gradually. This book sums up: It presents a well-founded inventory and critical reflection of »old« and »new« research approaches.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aComputerspiele. 4aComputerspielforschung. 4aDigitale Medien. 4aGame Design. 4aMassenkultur. 4aMedien. 4aMedienkultur. 4aMedienwissenschaft. 4aMedienästhetik. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh  aComputer Games Research.  aComputer Games.  aDigital Media.  aGame Design.  aMass Culture.  aMedia Aesthetics.  aMedia Culture.  aMedia Studies.  aMedia.1 aAbend, Pablo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAckermann, Judlth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeil, Benjamin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeil, Benjamin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBogost, lan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBojahr, Phtltpp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonner, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCzauderna, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreyermuth, Gundolf S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreyermuth, Gundolf S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGotto, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGotto, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 